There is no information available for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44C472C3864CC35E2D2BA4CB1991FE09" pageId="6" pageNumber="463" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="0C612148864CC35E2D2BA4CB1991FE09" blockId="6.[1363,2573,277,553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="3EAAFD5A864CC35E2D2BA4CB16EEFE5E" bold="true" box="[1366,1712,399,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. Hoffmanns’s Titi is relatively well protected by the isolation of its geographic distribution. It is present in Amazonia National Park and Itaituba National Forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
